TY  - JOUR
T1  - Specification tests for distributional assumptions in the Tobit model
AU  - Newey, Whitney K.
JO  - Journal of Econometrics
VL  - 34
IS  - 1
SP  - 125
EP  - 145
PY  - 1987
DA  - 1987/01/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(87)90070-4
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407687900704
AB  - The recent development of distribution robust estimators for the censored regression model allows for the construction of specification tests of the normality and homoskedasticity assumption of the Tobit model. This paper considers Hausman (1978) specification tests for the Tobit model that are based on Powell's (1986) symmetrically censored least squares estimator. Testing for models with explanatory variables that are endogeneous is considered, as well as the simpler case where the explanatory variables are exogenous. Testing of the maintained conditional symmetry assumption of the symmetrically censored least squares estimator is also considered. The tests are implemented in an empirical example of a model of female labor supply.
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - Non-parametric testing of discrete panel data models
AU  - Lee, Lung-Fei
JO  - Journal of Econometrics
VL  - 34
IS  - 1
SP  - 147
EP  - 177
PY  - 1987
DA  - 1987/01/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(87)90071-6
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407687900716
AB  - The stochastic structures of the homogeneous multinomial process, the heterogeneous multinomial process, the Markov chain and the heterogeneous Markov chain are analyzed within a discrete panel data framework. A general theoretical and computationally tractible framework to test the stochastic structures is proposed. Our testing framework is non-parametric in nature and can incorporate the presence of time-varying exogenous variables and can be applied to the general polychotomous response cases. Asymptotically optimal tests can be easily implemented. The LM tests for the stochastic structures are simply to test certain orthogonality conditions with residuals.
ER  - 

