AB  - This paper discusses the problem of assessing the predictive power of a model in the class of limited dependent variable models. The use of dummy variables in this context in standard regression models has been discussed in Salkever (1976), however problems emerge if such an approach is taken when the dummy appears in a limit of an integral that has to be evaluated. The paper proposes tests of predictive power which circumvent these problems.
